=E2=80=A2 <i>no</i> concave (greater than 180=C2=B0) internal angles <br>
=E2=80=A2 <i>no</i> parallel sides<br>
=E2=80=A2 two pairs of equal, adjacent sides (a and b)<br>

=E2=80=A2 two equal angles (B and C) called non-vertex angles<br>
=E2=80=A2 diagonals which <i>always</i> meet at right angles<br>
=E2=80=A2 a diagonal, called the axis of symmetry (line AD), that bisects t=
he other diagonal (line BC), bisects the vertex angles (A and D) <i>and</i>=
 divides the kite into two congruent triangles (ABD and ACD)<br>
=E2=80=A2 a diagonal (line BC) that divides the kite into two isoceles tria=
ngles (ABC and BCD)<br>

